                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16493294" author="tsteinmaurer" created="Tue, 29 May 2018 09:27:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch is based on Cassandra 3.11 and for Linux only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16493375" author="kurtg" created="Tue, 29 May 2018 11:09:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 from me. I can&apos;t see any valid reason why you would want to have more than 1 GC thread for nodetool. All the work is done within Cassandra, so there shouldn&apos;t be any adverse effects to only having 1 GC thread for the tool (famous last words).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16493458" author="spodxx@gmail.com" created="Tue, 29 May 2018 12:18:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is probably not really nodetool specific, but an acknowledged JVM issue, fixed in Java 9.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=6858051&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=6858051&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16493468" author="jasobrown" created="Tue, 29 May 2018 12:22:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lgtm. committed as sha &lt;tt&gt;b8cbdde2b854229d950d7087ac1847f8453d2b1e&lt;/tt&gt;. Thanks, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tsteinmaurer&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tsteinmaurer&quot;&gt;tsteinmaurer&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16493474" author="tsteinmaurer" created="Tue, 29 May 2018 12:26:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jasobrown&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jasobrown&quot;&gt;jasobrown&lt;/a&gt;, thanks! Sorry for being a pain, but any chance to get this back-ported for 2.1+?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16493508" author="jasobrown" created="Tue, 29 May 2018 13:05:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2.1 is critical fixes only, and 2.2 is close in that category. I debated if this patch should go into 3.0 or not, but then opted for stability in the 3.0 branch. Also, your patch as for 3.11, so I used that as my base barnch &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
